As if they'd all taken leave of their
senses.

42
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:17,000 
For ten years the small kingdoms were
at war.

43
00:03:17,840 --> 00:03:22,360 
Peter grew into an upright young man.
But his father was losing his strenght,

44
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:26,080 
grieving for the good wife he had lost.

45
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:34,640 
Steward...

46
00:03:35,320 --> 00:03:37,880 
You maintained war
would make our fortune.

47
00:03:37,960 --> 00:03:39,640 
Where is that fortune?

48
00:03:39,720 --> 00:03:43,280 
To make it we'd have needed 5,000 ducats

49
00:03:43,360 --> 00:03:46,280 
for an army - to win!

50
00:03:46,360 --> 00:03:49,000 
Why did you make war then?

51
00:03:49,080 --> 00:03:51,520 
I keep you,
to keep track of these things!

52
00:03:51,600 --> 00:03:53,600 
It's no fun ruling.

53
00:03:53,680 --> 00:03:55,440 
I like hunting!

54
00:03:55,520 --> 00:03:58,440 
After your wars there isn't a partridge
in my woods.

55
00:03:58,520 --> 00:04:01,480 
If we set up an army.

56
00:04:01,560 --> 00:04:04,120 
I'd need 5,000.

57
00:04:04,200 --> 00:04:07,640 
You've gone mad.
Damn it, where are my...

58
00:04:07,960 --> 00:04:09,680 
Keys?

59
00:04:09,920 --> 00:04:11,640 
Keys!

60
00:04:13,760 --> 00:04:15,760 
Good morning.
- Good morning.

61
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:18,200 
Don't you know
where my cash-box keys are?

62
00:04:18,280 --> 00:04:19,720 
Adela!
- No, Pappa.

63
00:04:19,920 --> 00:04:21,760 
Angelina?
- Oh, Pappa.

64
00:04:21,840 --> 00:04:24,320 
Where can they be?

65
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:26,440 
Adela!

66
00:04:26,520 --> 00:04:29,560 
But this is where you usually put them!
- Here!

67
00:04:30,800 --> 00:04:33,840 
I never put it there.
- There?

68
00:04:34,040 --> 00:04:35,680 
Here!
- There!

69
00:04:38,960 --> 00:04:41,560 
That's all...

70
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:45,400 
AII? ...our cash.
- You promised me a new dress!

71
00:04:46,680 --> 00:04:49,960 
The steward needs money a new army.
- 5,000.

72
00:04:50,040 --> 00:04:52,320 
Adela never moans about new dresses.

73
00:04:52,400 --> 00:04:56,480 
Because I give her mine
and then have nothing to wear.

74
00:04:56,560 --> 00:04:59,280 
Let go,
this is State money.

75
00:05:01,760 --> 00:05:04,800 
Don't cry, Angelina,

76
00:05:04,880 --> 00:05:07,040 
this dress is good enough for me.
- Shut up, you goose.

77
00:05:07,400 --> 00:05:09,880 
I'll never get married this way.

78
00:05:10,920 --> 00:05:14,600 
Must I do it all myself, you lazybones?

79
00:05:15,840 --> 00:05:18,720 
You're such a help, my boy.

80
00:05:20,880 --> 00:05:23,000 
Ah, the steward...

81
00:05:23,080 --> 00:05:25,480 
Go watch your pots.
- We are honoured.

82
00:05:25,880 --> 00:05:29,240 
Have you thought of getting married,
Dorothy?

83
00:05:31,240 --> 00:05:33,080 
The man in my heart

84
00:05:33,160 --> 00:05:35,960 
would hardly choose me.

85
00:05:36,360 --> 00:05:38,960 
How about Machal the miller?

86
00:05:39,040 --> 00:05:40,000 
Machal?

87
00:05:40,080 --> 00:05:42,360 
That old geezer?

88
00:05:42,440 --> 00:05:46,800 
I thought you were more cunning.
If a bright young woman married him

89
00:05:46,880 --> 00:05:50,720 
the mill could soon hers.

90
00:05:50,960 --> 00:05:52,800 
But he's got a son.

91
00:05:52,880 --> 00:05:55,040 
That can be arranged.

92
00:05:55,120 --> 00:05:57,320 
Where did that cat come from?

93
00:05:57,400 --> 00:05:59,280 
In the kitchen?

94
00:06:15,840 --> 00:06:18,160 
Good morning, neighbour!

95
00:06:18,400 --> 00:06:20,320 
Good morning.

96
00:06:20,680 --> 00:06:23,840 
Dear God, what a mess!
I was passing by,

97
00:06:23,920 --> 00:06:26,480 
something's burning,
would you like some help?

98
00:06:28,680 --> 00:06:30,440 
Thank you.

99
00:06:32,240 --> 00:06:35,160 
This is a woman's job.

100
00:06:57,840 --> 00:07:00,520 
There, aren't they lovely.

101
00:07:00,680 --> 00:07:02,640 
Help yourselves!
There's lots!

102
00:07:07,200 --> 00:07:10,400 
In a matter of weeks -
they were married.

103
00:07:11,960 --> 00:07:15,960 
If an old man wants to play the fool,

104
00:07:16,520 --> 00:07:18,840 
he marries a young woman.

105
00:07:19,080 --> 00:07:22,360 
For this we'll buy the field by the
pond.

106
00:07:22,960 --> 00:07:27,120 
The mill's enough, Dorothy,
a field would mean more work still!

107
00:07:28,160 --> 00:07:31,320 
But Frankie, you're so strong!

108
00:07:32,640 --> 00:07:35,000 
Surely you don't feel old?

109
00:07:35,080 --> 00:07:37,320 
Of course not.

110
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:40,880 
Mind you don't burn it.

111
00:07:43,080 --> 00:07:45,600 
Haven't you got a good wife?

112
00:07:47,080 --> 00:07:48,840 
I have.

113
00:07:49,520 --> 00:07:52,480 
Others would spend it all on clothes.

114
00:07:53,920 --> 00:07:56,680 
Why did you let the men go?

115
00:07:56,760 --> 00:08:00,840 
Whoever heard of two men doing all
the work?

116
00:08:01,120 --> 00:08:05,040 
You do nothing but lazy around.
We have no money to waste!

117
00:08:08,680 --> 00:08:11,400 
Dad, say something!

118
00:08:13,880 --> 00:08:17,520 
Dorothy is right, Peter.
We'll manage.

119
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:37,720 
Frankie!
There's a dance on tonight.

120
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:40,680 
You haven't forgotten, have you?

121
00:08:40,760 --> 00:08:42,920 
But Dorothy, I'm...
- Or do I go by myself?

122
00:08:43,800 --> 00:08:45,840 
No, Dorothy, no.

123
00:09:04,160 --> 00:09:06,920 
And now a gavotte!

124
00:09:07,040 --> 00:09:08,800 
Let's sit his out.

125
00:09:08,880 --> 00:09:11,200 
D'you want me to dance
with someone else?

126
00:09:11,280 --> 00:09:13,160 
No.
- Well then!

127
00:09:25,880 --> 00:09:27,720 
Faster!

128
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:37,280 
Frankie!

129
00:09:46,960 --> 00:09:50,120 
Poor unhappy me.
What'll I do without him?!

130
00:10:42,840 --> 00:10:45,360 
Once upon a time there was Hell.

131
00:10:45,800 --> 00:10:49,600 
There they had a pair of scales,
not to weigh people's pounds

132
00:10:50,200 --> 00:10:53,240 
but their sins.

133
00:10:54,080 --> 00:10:56,280 
There was no cheating it.

134
00:11:20,760 --> 00:11:23,160 
Stop!

135
00:11:27,360 --> 00:11:30,240 
Stand still and give me a report!

136
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:34,960 
Your Majesty, King of the Darkness,
Lucifer XIV.

137
00:11:35,040 --> 00:11:37,440 
I bear fresh news of Dorothy Machal.

138
00:11:37,520 --> 00:11:40,120 
Wait!

139
00:11:40,280 --> 00:11:43,800 
Where is the Book of Sins?
- It should have been here!

140
00:11:57,800 --> 00:12:00,440 
Her cup of sins has overflowed.

141
00:12:00,520 --> 00:12:02,480 
Here's the Book.
- Scram!

142
00:12:02,560 --> 00:12:04,360 
Come here!

143
00:12:04,440 --> 00:12:06,680 
You left your post?!

144
00:12:06,760 --> 00:12:08,680 
The Bat has taken over!
- Quiet!

145
00:12:10,040 --> 00:12:12,800 
I thought...
- Silence!

146
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:21,000 
Scram!

147
00:12:21,400 --> 00:12:24,480 
Dorothy Machal, page 1027,

148
00:12:24,560 --> 00:12:26,960 
line eight.
- I can see.

149
00:12:27,320 --> 00:12:29,440 
Line eight...

150
00:12:29,520 --> 00:12:31,800 
So I see.
I look - and see!

151
00:12:31,880 --> 00:12:34,000 
Yes, here.

152
00:12:34,880 --> 00:12:37,080 
You impertinent devil.

153
00:12:40,520 --> 00:12:42,640 
What do I see?

154
00:12:44,840 --> 00:12:47,000 
What do we see?

155
00:12:47,360 --> 00:12:49,480 
Stand still!
Don't move!

156
00:12:56,960 --> 00:12:59,240 
I said don't move!

157
00:13:07,560 --> 00:13:09,200 
That's my boot.

158
00:13:09,280 --> 00:13:11,800 
That was your boot.

159
00:13:13,640 --> 00:13:16,800 
A feather.
Where did it come from?

160
00:13:18,120 --> 00:13:20,520 
Come here, Cat!

161
00:13:21,120 --> 00:13:23,320 
Here, come on!

162
00:13:24,600 --> 00:13:26,640 
Let's see your teeth!

163
00:13:26,720 --> 00:13:29,080 
Teeth!

164
00:13:31,680 --> 00:13:33,680 
Your hands!

165
00:13:34,360 --> 00:13:36,560 
The other one!

166
00:13:37,560 --> 00:13:39,400 
It hurts!

167
00:13:40,040 --> 00:13:42,440 
All devils - line up!

168
00:13:56,400 --> 00:13:58,320 
No!

169
00:14:15,480 --> 00:14:17,520 
Come here!

170
00:15:08,640 --> 00:15:11,480 
A chicken!
All change back!

171
00:15:23,560 --> 00:15:25,840 
Your hand!
What is that?!

172
00:15:26,560 --> 00:15:27,520 
What is that?!

173
00:15:27,600 --> 00:15:29,600 
I was so terribly hungry!

174
00:15:29,680 --> 00:15:34,000 
I'll show you, wanting meat.

175
00:15:35,320 --> 00:15:37,840 
I hereby degrade you to rabbit!

176
00:15:40,400 --> 00:15:44,640 
That was one single feather!

177
00:15:46,080 --> 00:15:48,840 
Were it not for my intervention...

178
00:15:50,040 --> 00:15:53,520 
the Book of Sins'd have been destroyed!

179
00:15:57,840 --> 00:16:00,200 
So was my advice good, Dorothy?

180
00:16:00,280 --> 00:16:02,640 
Very good.
Do help yourself,

181
00:16:02,720 --> 00:16:05,600 
we're not stingy like at the castle.

182
00:16:05,680 --> 00:16:09,040 
Yes.
How pretty you are today, Dorothy.

183
00:16:12,680 --> 00:16:14,360 
A young one.

184
00:16:19,720 --> 00:16:21,760 
Tender?

185
00:16:34,920 --> 00:16:38,520 
I hurried over
to tell you -

186
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:43,920 
how sorry I am.

187
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:49,200 
You didn't even know my father.

188
00:16:49,320 --> 00:16:51,920 
Go and mend the roof, it's leaking.

189
00:16:52,280 --> 00:16:54,440 
Did you hear me?

190
00:17:02,560 --> 00:17:04,400 
The lazy lout.

191
00:17:37,720 --> 00:17:40,800 
Get down at once!
Take that of the chimney!

192
00:17:40,880 --> 00:17:44,120 
I am mending the roof

193
00:17:44,200 --> 00:17:46,200 
as you told me to.

194
00:17:46,280 --> 00:17:47,680 
Did you hear me?

195
00:17:47,760 --> 00:17:50,880 
Climb down at once,
you young rascal!

196
00:17:51,240 --> 00:17:53,120 
At once!

197
00:17:53,960 --> 00:17:56,240 
You're right.

198
00:17:57,800 --> 00:17:59,560 
I'm going.

199
00:18:01,880 --> 00:18:03,400 
No.

200
00:18:03,480 --> 00:18:06,520 
You dropped something.

201
00:18:06,600 --> 00:18:09,640 
Help me, woman.
What is this?

202
00:18:09,720 --> 00:18:11,080 
It smells horrid.

203
00:18:11,160 --> 00:18:14,320 
Where're you going?
You haven't chopped the wood yet!

204
00:18:14,400 --> 00:18:16,160 
Let the steward chop it for you!

205
00:18:16,240 --> 00:18:19,120 
I'll be back when you're gone!

206
00:18:21,600 --> 00:18:23,680 
This will cost you dear!

207
00:18:24,280 --> 00:18:27,840 
You lot her cheat you out of everything?

208
00:18:28,520 --> 00:18:30,720 
Where's your common sense?

209
00:18:30,800 --> 00:18:33,960 
I didn't leave everything.
Look!

210
00:18:37,640 --> 00:18:41,280 
My mother's.
The ring I'll give my bride one day.

211
00:18:50,120 --> 00:18:53,200 
Peek-a-boo!
I've got the warrant for arrest

212
00:18:54,320 --> 00:18:58,200 
for that stepson of yours.

213
00:18:58,960 --> 00:19:01,080 
When his Majesty signs it

214
00:19:01,160 --> 00:19:04,880 
the mill will soon be ours.
I mean yours.

215
00:19:08,360 --> 00:19:10,960 
A life sentence.
- A life sentence.

216
00:19:11,840 --> 00:19:13,960 
Good!
- Isn't it?

217
00:19:14,040 --> 00:19:16,840 
But it'll cost something.

218
00:19:22,920 --> 00:19:25,080 
No, no.

219
00:19:25,440 --> 00:19:28,040 
There was no need for that.
Put you'll need some for his Majesty,

220
00:19:28,120 --> 00:19:30,680 
He's so money-minded.

221
00:19:34,400 --> 00:19:36,240 
Angeline!

222
00:19:38,800 --> 00:19:40,440 
Come on!

223
00:19:40,520 --> 00:19:42,880 
Wait!

224
00:19:44,920 --> 00:19:46,920 
Wait for me!

225
00:19:51,320 --> 00:19:52,920 
Caught you!

226
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:56,720 
Look what you've done!
Torn my only dress!

227
00:19:56,800 --> 00:19:59,520 
I'm sorry, Angelina.
Forgive me.

228
00:19:59,600 --> 00:20:01,800 
Come on!
- We can darn it!

229
00:20:01,880 --> 00:20:03,760 
No we can't.

230
00:20:03,920 --> 00:20:07,640 
I am willing to ignore

231
00:20:07,720 --> 00:20:09,960 
that he wanted to kill me,

232
00:20:10,040 --> 00:20:14,320 
but he robbed his mother,
that sadly berieved widow,

233
00:20:14,800 --> 00:20:18,200 
and he up and left her

234
00:20:18,280 --> 00:20:19,840 
with the whole mill to look after!

235
00:20:19,920 --> 00:20:22,760 
What do I do?
I didn't bring up her son!

236
00:20:22,840 --> 00:20:25,200 
No, your Majesty!

237
00:20:25,280 --> 00:20:27,800 
You could jail him.

238
00:20:27,880 --> 00:20:31,560 
He is an incredibly dangerous man.

239
00:20:31,640 --> 00:20:33,440 
Look, come back some other time.

240
00:20:33,680 --> 00:20:36,240 
I'm busy right now.

241
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:54,920 
So he's a naughty boy?

242
00:20:55,120 --> 00:20:56,800 
I'm a helpless woman,

243
00:20:56,880 --> 00:20:59,760 
I'm afraid of him!

244
00:20:59,840 --> 00:21:02,960 
You're telling me,
children are a worry.

245
00:21:03,160 --> 00:21:04,800 
Yes.

246
00:21:06,640 --> 00:21:09,280 
Here.

247
00:21:09,360 --> 00:21:11,800 
Pappa, now you'll admit

248
00:21:11,880 --> 00:21:14,560 
that I need a new dress!

249
00:21:14,640 --> 00:21:16,440 
Here.

250
00:21:16,520 --> 00:21:18,160 
What has Petr Machal done,
that you want him jailed?

251
00:21:18,240 --> 00:21:20,600 
Children...
- May I?

252
00:21:22,960 --> 00:21:24,560 
There.

253
00:21:24,720 --> 00:21:28,600 
Would your Majesty take up the pen

254
00:21:30,600 --> 00:21:34,080 
and sign here, please.

255
00:21:34,320 --> 00:21:36,560 
Sign up, Pappa!

256
00:21:36,640 --> 00:21:37,920 
After you've ascertained

257
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:41,160 
who's in the right!
- Oh, come on.

258
00:21:44,280 --> 00:21:47,000 
Right indeed.

259
00:21:50,480 --> 00:21:53,040 
Yes.

260
00:21:57,000 --> 00:21:59,040 
Joseph the Handsome.

261
00:22:06,840 --> 00:22:09,080 
I didn't hear you say good day.

262
00:22:09,840 --> 00:22:13,160 
On his Majesty's decision
you are under arrest.

263
00:22:13,920 --> 00:22:15,480 
No.

264
00:22:15,600 --> 00:22:17,640 
Arrested?
Why?

265
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:20,560 
They'll explain at the castle.

266
00:22:31,320 --> 00:22:32,960 
Come on!

267
00:22:38,400 --> 00:22:40,560 
Go away!

268
00:22:51,840 --> 00:22:53,800 
Come on up!

