00:49:22,200 --> 00:49:24,840 
I'm no soldier, I'm a devil!

535
00:49:25,600 --> 00:49:28,160 
I've come for a widow?!

536
00:49:28,520 --> 00:49:31,440 
A widow? A devil?

537
00:49:31,640 --> 00:49:33,400 
You wait!

538
00:49:41,600 --> 00:49:44,440 
Arms up!
One, two, three, four!

539
00:49:49,800 --> 00:49:52,600 
Arms down!
One, two, three, four!

540
00:49:57,800 --> 00:50:00,600 
Forward march!
One, two, three, four!

541
00:50:02,680 --> 00:50:05,520 
Halt!

542
00:50:08,480 --> 00:50:11,240 
Call that marching?
Your name and rank!

543
00:50:11,400 --> 00:50:14,560 
Devil of Horse rank, no Wolf.

544
00:50:15,520 --> 00:50:18,320 
What?
You dare make fun of me?

545
00:50:20,920 --> 00:50:24,960 
Down - up!

546
00:50:26,920 --> 00:50:29,160 
Down!

547
00:50:31,120 --> 00:50:33,120 
Up!
Down!

548
00:50:37,160 --> 00:50:39,200 
Up!
Down!

549
00:50:40,600 --> 00:50:42,680 
Come in to the garden.

550
00:50:42,760 --> 00:50:44,560 
Wait.

551
00:50:44,960 --> 00:50:47,000 
Down!
Up!

552
00:50:48,160 --> 00:50:50,160 
Down!
Up!

553
00:50:54,400 --> 00:50:57,440 
Arms at the ready!

554
00:51:01,400 --> 00:51:03,480 
That's rebellion!
Throw your weapon down!

555
00:51:05,840 --> 00:51:07,880 
What's that?

556
00:51:07,960 --> 00:51:10,640 
Machal, back in line!
What did I say?

557
00:51:14,480 --> 00:51:16,760 
Get back, Machal!

558
00:51:16,840 --> 00:51:20,320 
20 days' jail
and 50 lashings!

559
00:51:21,760 --> 00:51:24,400 
Come back!

560
00:51:25,280 --> 00:51:27,040 
Did you see that?

561
00:51:27,120 --> 00:51:29,720 
Peter must have a good heart.

562
00:51:29,800 --> 00:51:32,960 
You and your Peter.

563
00:51:33,160 --> 00:51:36,080 
Mine?

564
00:51:36,200 --> 00:51:38,800 
You know he wants you.
And you?

565
00:51:39,560 --> 00:51:43,040 
Exactly.
Men need tricking, you silly.

566
00:51:50,560 --> 00:51:52,880 
50 lashings.

567
00:51:53,400 --> 00:51:55,240 
They shout at you all day
make you roll in the mud.

568
00:51:55,320 --> 00:51:59,840 
And all because of that woman.

569
00:52:01,160 --> 00:52:03,240 
Surely you're not in love?

570
00:52:03,320 --> 00:52:05,080 
No fear.

571
00:52:05,160 --> 00:52:08,600 
I was to bring a bad widow to Hell.

572
00:52:09,960 --> 00:52:13,160 
Was it Dorothy Machal by any chance?

573
00:52:15,800 --> 00:52:17,720 
How do you know?

574
00:52:18,560 --> 00:52:20,280 
If anybody I know deserves hell,

575
00:52:20,360 --> 00:52:23,600 
it's my stepmother.

576
00:52:26,360 --> 00:52:29,160 
So you are Peter?

577
00:52:29,760 --> 00:52:32,240 
And you really are a devil.

578
00:52:32,720 --> 00:52:35,240 
I should say!

579
00:52:36,840 --> 00:52:41,440 
Oh, but I'm not any more.
I'd have to get my wolf's tail back.

580
00:52:43,400 --> 00:52:45,320 
A wolf's tail?

581
00:52:46,560 --> 00:52:50,400 
I can't go back to hell till I have it.

582
00:52:51,000 --> 00:52:53,400 
What do you mean, a wolf's tail?

583
00:52:54,480 --> 00:52:57,360 
I can't change back without it.

584
00:52:59,360 --> 00:53:01,480 
I don't get it.

585
00:53:04,040 --> 00:53:06,480 
Go clean out the stables.

586
00:53:24,040 --> 00:53:27,440 
Doesn't Princess Angelina

587
00:53:27,520 --> 00:53:29,400 
look lovely?

588
00:53:30,000 --> 00:53:33,360 
Our cash-box is empty,
the ceiling's coming down

589
00:53:33,600 --> 00:53:36,880 
and we hold balls for borrowed money.

590
00:53:37,160 --> 00:53:39,200 
Curtsy, Angelina!

591
00:53:39,280 --> 00:53:41,480 
To the green one.

592
00:53:41,760 --> 00:53:43,680 
It's all arranged.

593
00:53:43,760 --> 00:53:45,680 
Angelina, Curtsy.

594
00:53:45,760 --> 00:53:49,120 
Angelina will marry richest suitor,

595
00:53:49,320 --> 00:53:52,800 
we'll pay our debts and have some over.

596
00:53:53,400 --> 00:53:56,120 
Do you like any of them?

597
00:53:58,200 --> 00:54:00,520 
Whom do you like?

598
00:54:00,680 --> 00:54:03,520 
Who is the richest?

599
00:54:03,640 --> 00:54:06,280 
She says who is the richest?

600
00:54:06,360 --> 00:54:08,880 
Well, who is the richest?
- Who is??

601
00:54:08,960 --> 00:54:11,920 
Quietly.
I'll find out.

602
00:54:13,920 --> 00:54:17,280 
Can it be a dead wolf's tail?

603
00:54:17,880 --> 00:54:21,320 
Sure,
how'd you out it off a live one?

604
00:54:23,400 --> 00:54:27,440 
I know of one.
But how to got out of the barracks.

605
00:54:27,880 --> 00:54:29,640 
Wait!

606
00:54:30,960 --> 00:54:34,720 
Ah, for our lovely pub
ah, for their lovely grub,

607
00:54:37,240 --> 00:54:40,320 
the soup is so hot

608
00:54:40,640 --> 00:54:43,080 
the boor is with froth!

609
00:54:56,680 --> 00:54:58,640 
What's happening?

610
00:54:58,800 --> 00:55:00,800 
What's should be?

611
00:55:00,880 --> 00:55:02,520 
Nothing?
- Nothing.

612
00:55:03,160 --> 00:55:05,160 
Sure?
- Sure.

613
00:55:27,360 --> 00:55:30,240 
I know now who's the richest.

614
00:55:30,320 --> 00:55:33,040 
I've investigated.

615
00:55:33,240 --> 00:55:37,800 
According to ancient custom
the Princess will throw a golden apple,

616
00:55:38,600 --> 00:55:42,160 
the man it stops by will become
her husband.

617
00:55:43,480 --> 00:55:47,240 
But that's not gold.

618
00:55:48,160 --> 00:55:49,440 
No, I shall gold it.

619
00:55:49,520 --> 00:55:52,160 
What if it rolls some Pauper?

620
00:55:52,240 --> 00:55:54,400 
Yes.
The ball is actually made of iron.

621
00:55:55,720 --> 00:55:58,120 
And this stone will make it stop

622
00:55:58,200 --> 00:56:01,720 
by the richest of the suitors.

623
00:56:03,320 --> 00:56:06,280 
Try pulling it away.

624
00:56:06,360 --> 00:56:08,800 
I can't.

625
00:56:09,720 --> 00:56:11,800 
I'll do it.

626
00:56:13,840 --> 00:56:16,480 
What is this stone?

627
00:56:16,560 --> 00:56:20,920 
It comes from Magnet Mountain

628
00:56:21,000 --> 00:56:23,120 
and attracts all iron objects.

629
00:56:24,160 --> 00:56:27,720 
I did say all iron objects.

630
00:57:12,840 --> 00:57:14,920 
Yes, but...

631
00:57:15,000 --> 00:57:17,440 
I'd prefer...

632
00:57:17,520 --> 00:57:20,120 
The army is important,

633
00:57:20,240 --> 00:57:23,360 
believe me.

634
00:58:07,680 --> 00:58:10,760 
Hello, officer!
What are you doing here?

635
00:58:13,480 --> 00:58:16,360 
How lovely you look, Princess.

636
00:58:16,440 --> 00:58:18,960 
And gallant, too.

637
00:58:19,040 --> 00:58:21,960 
But you haven't asked me dance yet!

638
00:58:22,400 --> 00:58:25,840 
Permit me to rectify my mistake.

639
00:58:31,200 --> 00:58:35,360 
For so long I've been wanting...
- Long?

640
00:58:35,440 --> 00:58:37,680 
I don't know you, you must be new.

641
00:58:37,760 --> 00:58:39,920 
Good evening, Peter.
- Good evening.

642
00:58:40,000 --> 00:58:43,040 
That's Machal, the young miller.

643
00:58:43,560 --> 00:58:47,200 
Where did you steal the uniform?
How dare you?

644
00:58:48,120 --> 00:58:49,280 
Guards!

645
00:58:49,360 --> 00:58:51,560 
Wait, Angelina!

646
00:58:51,640 --> 00:58:54,000 
Guards!

647
00:58:55,080 --> 00:58:57,360 
I only wanted to see you.

648
00:58:57,440 --> 00:58:59,920 
Catch him!

649
00:59:00,000 --> 00:59:02,680 
Hurry up!
Throw him in prison!

650
00:59:19,200 --> 00:59:21,600 
Peter!
Hide in here!

651
00:59:26,160 --> 00:59:28,120 
He ran this way!

652
00:59:31,120 --> 00:59:32,760 
Come on!

653
00:59:37,640 --> 00:59:40,440 
Thank you, Princess.
- Run!

654
00:59:44,080 --> 00:59:47,440 
Prince, do you want our Princess?

655
00:59:51,320 --> 00:59:54,080 
I'd give anything...

656
01:00:00,720 --> 01:00:04,120 
Put this in your shoe and she is yours.

657
01:00:05,800 --> 01:00:09,560 
According to ancient custom
the Princess's husband

658
01:00:13,080 --> 01:00:16,520 
will be chosen...
justly... by this golden apple.

659
01:00:20,320 --> 01:00:22,640 
He to whom it rolls will have her.

660
01:00:23,760 --> 01:00:26,440 
As his wife!

661
01:00:26,640 --> 01:00:28,640 
As his wife.

662
01:00:37,400 --> 01:00:39,880 
The apple.
Roll it towards the left.

663
01:00:55,000 --> 01:00:57,040 
No!

664
01:00:58,840 --> 01:01:00,760 
Help!

665
01:01:02,800 --> 01:01:04,760 
Pappa!

666
01:01:07,680 --> 01:01:11,040 
I'll tell my Pappa and
he'll declare war!

667
01:01:11,120 --> 01:01:13,600 
Congratulations, you won.

668
01:01:13,680 --> 01:01:17,080 
My Pappa will make war on you.
Carry him away.

669
01:01:22,280 --> 01:01:25,120 
Pappa'll make war!

670
01:01:34,840 --> 01:01:37,960 
Take this thing out of my shoe!

671
01:01:38,760 --> 01:01:41,680 
What thing?

672
01:01:41,760 --> 01:01:43,440 
We've been cheated!

673
01:01:43,520 --> 01:01:46,240 
Take my shoe off!

674
01:01:46,560 --> 01:01:48,240 
We want the money we lent you!

675
01:01:48,320 --> 01:01:50,360 
We've been tricked!
- Silence!

676
01:01:50,440 --> 01:01:53,440 
We'll declare war together!

677
01:01:54,480 --> 01:01:57,960 
Take my shoe off!
My Pappa'll make war on you!

678
01:01:59,920 --> 01:02:01,920 
Sure.

679
01:02:03,160 --> 01:02:05,320 
What will we do?

680
01:02:08,480 --> 01:02:11,120 
Luckily we have a strong army.

681
01:02:12,880 --> 01:02:15,840 
There's a parade tomorrow.

682
01:02:15,920 --> 01:02:17,720 
What?
- A parade.

683
01:02:18,400 --> 01:02:20,840 
We have a parade?

684
01:02:20,920 --> 01:02:22,640 
Come and see.
- I'll come.

685
01:02:24,880 --> 01:02:28,680 
Action stations!

686
01:02:29,360 --> 01:02:33,160 
Dammit-all-to-hell
I said action stations!

687
01:02:34,320 --> 01:02:36,160 
Sound the alarm!

688
01:02:36,720 --> 01:02:38,760 
Attention!
Where is your uniform, you stupid?

689
01:02:43,360 --> 01:02:45,120 
Attention!

690
01:02:46,000 --> 01:02:48,040 
Attention!
Attention!

691
01:03:27,280 --> 01:03:29,040 
This way.

692
01:03:30,280 --> 01:03:32,680 
Excuse me, where's the door.

693
01:04:04,000 --> 01:04:05,600 
Fire!

694
01:04:15,200 --> 01:04:16,840 
Come!

695
01:04:27,280 --> 01:04:29,160 
My dress!

696
01:04:48,360 --> 01:04:52,000 
Corporal!
Is this what you call a strong army?

697
01:05:05,160 --> 01:05:07,040 
Catch him!

698
01:05:08,800 --> 01:05:11,000 
Bring my horse!

699
01:05:21,040 --> 01:05:23,640 
Backwards again!

700
01:05:24,080 --> 01:05:26,080 
What?
- Turn me round!

701
01:05:26,160 --> 01:05:29,320 
Turn the horse round!
- Not the horse, me!

702
01:05:56,080 --> 01:05:57,840 
Wait.

703
01:06:00,880 --> 01:06:02,600 
Now.

704
01:06:11,400 --> 01:06:13,560 
Dorothy!
Dorothy!

705
01:06:30,840 --> 01:06:33,160 
Let me go!

706
01:06:36,000 --> 01:06:38,160 
Leave me alone!
Help!

707
01:06:39,680 --> 01:06:41,520 
Help!
No!

708
01:06:54,520 --> 01:06:56,880 
Follow them!
Encircle them!

709
01:06:57,840 --> 01:07:00,200 
Quickly!

710
01:07:02,320 --> 01:07:04,720 
Everybody here!

711
01:07:05,600 --> 01:07:07,600 
Help!

712
01:07:09,600 --> 01:07:11,320 
Peter!

713
01:07:12,440 --> 01:07:14,600 
Give it to me.

714
01:07:14,680 --> 01:07:16,640 
Come on, Peter!

715
01:07:19,520 --> 01:07:21,600 
Follow them quickly!

716
01:07:21,800 --> 01:07:24,000 
We must get them!

717
01:07:26,320 --> 01:07:28,080 
How's that?

718
01:07:28,160 --> 01:07:31,920 
This doesn't load anywhere.
Dammit-all-to-hell!

719
01:07:32,640 --> 01:07:35,800 
You're ready for the gallows, Machal!

720
01:07:38,120 --> 01:07:41,640 
Hell's bells and cocker shells!

721
01:07:44,080 --> 01:07:46,840 
The gallows for you!

722
01:07:48,920 --> 01:07:51,320 
I snapped my sword!

723
01:07:53,160 --> 01:07:55,840 
My dear boy!

724
01:07:55,920 --> 01:07:58,120 
How happy I am to see you.

725
01:08:15,840 --> 01:08:18,080 
Good, she's sinking!

726
01:08:26,320 --> 01:08:28,680 
She's ours!

727
01:08:31,760 --> 01:08:33,720 
Take her!

728
01:08:36,800 --> 01:08:38,960 
She broke our scales.

729
01:08:39,040 --> 01:08:40,720 
Come here.

730
01:08:41,320 --> 01:08:43,680 
What do we do with him?

731
01:08:43,920 --> 01:08:47,960 
Leave me here for a few days.
They want to hang me.

732
01:08:49,080 --> 01:08:51,080 
Let go!

733
01:08:51,760 --> 01:08:54,280 
Take your hands away you hairy monster!

734
01:08:54,360 --> 01:08:56,520 
Help!

735
01:08:56,640 --> 01:08:58,800 
Let me go!

736
01:08:59,080 --> 01:09:01,480 
Don't touch me!

737
01:09:01,560 --> 01:09:03,720 
No,
help!

738
01:09:03,800 --> 01:09:06,240 
Help!
Help!

739
01:09:21,000 --> 01:09:24,040 
This is an ultimatum!
The ceiling's coming down.

740
01:09:27,280 --> 01:09:30,560 
Either I return their money within
the month

741
01:09:30,640 --> 01:09:34,320 
or they'll declare war.

742
01:09:35,960 --> 01:09:38,360 
Signed - all nine kingdoms.

743
01:09:40,400 --> 01:09:43,440 
Where am I to find the money?

744
01:09:47,280 --> 01:09:49,840 
How about selling the castle?

745
01:09:50,040 --> 01:09:53,400 
Are you mad?
Sell the roof over my head?

746
01:09:55,480 --> 01:09:59,000 
Actually, who'd buy the old ruin.

747
01:10:01,040 --> 01:10:04,520 
This castle was built
in the 12th century by my ancestors,

748
01:10:05,240 --> 01:10:09,200 
Ferdinand the Handsome and Josephine
the Mad.

749
01:10:12,160 --> 01:10:16,280 
Maybe I'd buy it off you,

750
01:10:21,800 --> 01:10:24,240 
to do you a favour.

751
01:10:29,120 --> 01:10:32,600 
The water strokes the pebbles

752
01:10:38,760 --> 01:10:42,320 
tenderly and softly
that is love.

753
01:10:49,520 --> 01:10:53,080 
Tenderly and softly
that is love.

754
01:11:01,960 --> 01:11:06,880 
Peter, dearest Peter,

755
01:11:10,640 --> 01:11:13,200 
who'll tell you that we two

756
01:11:13,680 --> 01:11:16,560 
are made for each other.

757
01:11:27,120 --> 01:11:28,960 
Get up!

758
01:11:29,600 --> 01:11:31,800 
The Devil never sleeps!

759
01:11:32,080 --> 01:11:34,800 
He did all this in a few days.

760
01:11:34,880 --> 01:11:37,680 
Leave that be and come here!

761
01:11:37,760 --> 01:11:41,520 
What do you think you're doing?
All this work down here?!

762
01:11:41,600 --> 01:11:42,920 
You'll spoil our reputation!

763
01:11:43,000 --> 01:11:46,520 
Make three wishes
and back to Earth with you!

764
01:11:47,160 --> 01:11:50,360 
One wish -
take me back home.

765
01:11:51,880 --> 01:11:54,560 
Of course, I will.
But what else?

766
01:11:54,960 --> 01:11:57,040 
Wait a minute.

767
01:12:07,240 --> 01:12:08,840 
Ask for this.

768
01:12:08,920 --> 01:12:11,520 
Such a scruffy old coat?
- It's magic.

769
01:12:12,160 --> 01:12:15,240 
He who wears it finds a ducat

770
01:12:15,320 --> 01:12:17,440 
in his pocket every time.

771
01:12:18,520 --> 01:12:20,760 
What is your wish?

772
01:12:20,840 --> 01:12:22,880 
To go back to Earth

773
01:12:22,960 --> 01:12:25,720 
to fetch the Corporal!

774
01:12:25,800 --> 01:12:28,040 
I'm coming with you.

775
01:12:28,120 --> 01:12:31,480 
All right.
You may take the coat.

776
01:12:35,240 --> 01:12:37,280 
And your grandmother.

777
01:12:37,880 --> 01:12:41,040 
I'll let Johnny go under the condition

778
01:12:41,680 --> 01:12:45,840 
that he brings the Corporal and
the Steward.

779
01:12:49,240 --> 01:12:52,200 
All right.
But won't they hang me?

780
01:12:54,600 --> 01:12:57,880 
With that coat on you are protected.

781
01:12:57,960 --> 01:13:00,040 
Put it on!

782
01:13:02,240 --> 01:13:04,320 
But don't forget -

783
01:13:04,400 --> 01:13:07,880 
when you take it off you lose all
powers.

784
01:13:13,160 --> 01:13:15,280 
May we go?

785
01:13:16,040 --> 01:13:18,320 
Let's see you.
Yes, you may!

786
01:13:23,040 --> 01:13:26,080 
Whom do we fetch first,
the Steward or the Corporal?

787
01:13:26,160 --> 01:13:28,680 
I'm going home to bake some cakes.

788
01:13:29,640 --> 01:13:32,960 
We're going to the pub.

789
01:13:33,040 --> 01:13:34,600 
Not even Lucifer
will get me to the pub.

790
01:13:34,680 --> 01:13:37,560 
That's where all my troubles began!

791
01:13:37,640 --> 01:13:39,480 
So I'll make the sacrifice and go.

792
01:13:39,560 --> 01:13:42,440 
You keep watch outside.
- You're great.

793
01:13:42,520 --> 01:13:44,400 
The devil!
The devil!

794
01:13:44,680 --> 01:13:46,360 
The devil!

795
01:13:47,080 --> 01:13:49,440 
How did they recognize you?
Me? Look at yourself!

796
01:14:01,160 --> 01:14:02,920 
Potato soup.

797
01:14:03,000 --> 01:14:04,640 
A full plate, please!

798
01:14:04,720 --> 01:14:07,080 
Pork with sauerkraut.
- Yes, Sir.

799
01:14:08,360 --> 01:14:10,160 
Goulash.

800
01:14:10,360 --> 01:14:12,160 
With bread.

801
01:14:12,240 --> 01:14:14,600 
And cream-cheese dumplings.

802
01:14:15,800 --> 01:14:18,120 
Right,
but can you pay?

803
01:14:30,200 --> 01:14:33,440 
Your servant, Milord -
at first sight I thought...

804
01:14:34,600 --> 01:14:37,840 
that you're...

805
01:14:38,280 --> 01:14:40,600 
What?

806
01:14:41,120 --> 01:14:42,960 
The devil!

807
01:14:43,120 --> 01:14:45,080 
Oh no.

808
01:14:45,160 --> 01:14:47,720 
I'm no devil.
I only look that way.

809
01:14:47,800 --> 01:14:50,920 
Take a seat,
it won't be long.

810
01:15:27,720 --> 01:15:30,000 
Take them.
They're yours.

811
01:15:55,800 --> 01:15:57,840 
Lots of money you say?

812
01:15:57,920 --> 01:16:01,280 
Must be a foreigner.

813
01:16:01,640 --> 01:16:04,120 
He's throwing ducats around.

814
01:16:04,320 --> 01:16:06,120 
Ducats?

815
01:16:06,200 --> 01:16:08,640 
He hands out as many as they ask for.

816
01:16:08,720 --> 01:16:11,040 
But Angelina.
- He must be mad.

817
01:16:11,840 --> 01:16:15,080 
See?
- Dress up as a pauper and go!

818
01:16:15,520 --> 01:16:18,880 
We can't miss such a chance!

819
01:16:21,320 --> 01:16:23,320 
82
- 82, thank you.

820
01:16:24,400 --> 01:16:28,080 
83
- 83, thank you.

821
01:16:28,160 --> 01:16:31,040 
84
- 84, thank you.

822
01:16:31,120 --> 01:16:32,800 
Come in!

823
01:16:35,080 --> 01:16:37,120 
Excuse me.

824
01:16:44,440 --> 01:16:46,520 
That's the Steward, you know!

825
01:16:46,880 --> 01:16:49,720 
I know.
I'll knock his feathered hat off.

826
01:16:49,800 --> 01:16:51,920 
And I'll catch him.

827
01:16:54,360 --> 01:16:57,040 
Where were we?
- 80

828
01:16:59,840 --> 01:17:02,640 
81
- 81

829
01:17:02,880 --> 01:17:05,480 
82
- 82

830
01:17:06,240 --> 01:17:08,840 
83
- 83

831
01:17:10,120 --> 01:17:12,200 
84

832
01:17:13,360 --> 01:17:15,720 
How dare you?

833
01:17:30,960 --> 01:17:34,640 
See this feather?
I have two, just in case!

834
01:17:42,000 --> 01:17:45,840 
Noble foreigner, you won't believe me

835
01:17:46,040 --> 01:17:50,040 
but I'm the poorest man around.

836
01:17:50,480 --> 01:17:53,280 
They all cheat me,
my children, the steward...

837
01:17:54,880 --> 01:17:57,880 
All I have but debts.

838
01:17:58,040 --> 01:18:00,760 
What would you like, your Majesty?

839
01:18:00,920 --> 01:18:02,680 
How can you know I'm...

840
01:18:04,920 --> 01:18:07,760 
Let's not play hide and seek.

841
01:18:07,840 --> 01:18:10,320 
How much do you need?

842
01:18:11,680 --> 01:18:14,000 
20,000 ducats.

843
01:18:20,520 --> 01:18:22,920 
All right,

844
01:18:23,320 --> 01:18:27,080 
but if you give me your daughter in
marriage.

845
01:18:31,320 --> 01:18:33,400 
30.000

846
01:18:38,720 --> 01:18:41,200 
I know it's a lot.

847
01:18:41,280 --> 01:18:43,280 
I don't understand.

848
01:18:43,360 --> 01:18:46,480 
I'm not scared, but I need help.

849
01:18:46,560 --> 01:18:48,080 
Help?

850
01:18:48,160 --> 01:18:51,400 
I have the feeling the devil
is after me.

851
01:18:53,040 --> 01:18:54,560 
The devil...

852
01:18:54,640 --> 01:18:56,560 
The devil.

853
01:19:03,080 --> 01:19:05,720 
I'll think of something.

854
01:19:05,880 --> 01:19:07,680 
Don't bother,

855
01:19:07,760 --> 01:19:10,080 
I've done that myself.

856
01:19:10,160 --> 01:19:13,520 
But I need a certain bunch of keys.

857
01:19:15,000 --> 01:19:17,040 
Keys?

858
01:19:20,920 --> 01:19:23,360 
I know the whereabouts of the steward
and corporal.

859
01:19:23,760 --> 01:19:25,760 
I heard them make arrangements.

860
01:19:25,840 --> 01:19:27,480 
But they've still got the feather.

861
01:19:27,560 --> 01:19:29,440 
Never mind.

862
01:19:29,840 --> 01:19:32,720 
Is the look dependable?

863
01:19:32,800 --> 01:19:36,160 
Sure,
it can be unlocked only from outside

864
01:19:37,200 --> 01:19:40,560 
and there stand the guards.
We are absolutely safe.

865
01:20:12,360 --> 01:20:14,880 
Come on, you...

866
01:20:35,560 --> 01:20:37,520 
Come here.

867
01:20:46,880 --> 01:20:50,600 
Come, little orphan,
join the others.

868
01:20:57,040 --> 01:21:00,120 
Here I am.
High time, too.

869
01:21:01,120 --> 01:21:03,240 
Corporal!

870
01:21:11,400 --> 01:21:13,200 
Quickly.

871
01:21:16,880 --> 01:21:19,040 
Sound the alarm!
Sound the alarm!

872
01:21:19,480 --> 01:21:21,640 
Which way?

873
01:21:26,760 --> 01:21:28,680 
What a lot of money!

874
01:21:28,760 --> 01:21:31,280 
I'll have some.

875
01:21:34,400 --> 01:21:36,480 
Help!

876
01:21:50,480 --> 01:21:52,280 
Where are they?

877
01:22:02,440 --> 01:22:04,520 
Soldiers, attention!

878
01:22:08,000 --> 01:22:09,960 
There they are!

879
01:22:10,040 --> 01:22:12,360 
Not there, this way.

880
01:22:13,240 --> 01:22:15,760 
The secret passage to the castle!

881
01:22:17,320 --> 01:22:19,800 
I'll help you.

882
01:22:25,800 --> 01:22:27,640 
This way?
Run!

883
01:22:43,480 --> 01:22:45,520 
Climb out!

884
01:22:48,680 --> 01:22:52,320 
No feathers.
- On our hats!

885
01:22:52,400 --> 01:22:54,560 
Back to the chest!

886
01:22:57,720 --> 01:22:59,680 
Quickly!
- This way!

887
01:23:00,240 --> 01:23:02,400 
I want to...

888
01:23:21,640 --> 01:23:23,840 
Wait here...

889
01:23:25,600 --> 01:23:27,560 
But Pappa...
- Who are you?

890
01:23:31,520 --> 01:23:33,640 
What are you doing here?

891
01:23:34,880 --> 01:23:36,640 
Come on!

892
01:23:43,040 --> 01:23:45,400 
Here we're safe.

893
01:23:45,880 --> 01:23:48,960 
And now we can disappear.

894
01:23:51,520 --> 01:23:55,120 
We're wasted in this stupid kingdom.

895
01:24:06,240 --> 01:24:08,320 
Thank you, Peter!

896
01:24:08,520 --> 01:24:11,000 
You'll have to marry him,
or he won't give us the money!

897
01:24:11,080 --> 01:24:13,480 
When he spruces up a bit...

898
01:24:13,560 --> 01:24:17,160 
I'm doing no such thing.
The Princess must marry me as I am.

899
01:24:18,000 --> 01:24:21,040 
I'll never marry such an eyesore!

900
01:24:21,120 --> 01:24:22,840 
Never!

901
01:24:22,960 --> 01:24:25,480 
Our debts!
Don't offend him.

902
01:24:25,560 --> 01:24:27,960 
I couldn't stand people seeing me
with such a fright!

903
01:24:28,040 --> 01:24:31,800 
As you like.
Goodbye.

904
01:24:33,360 --> 01:24:35,840 
Please, dear children!

905
01:24:36,240 --> 01:24:39,120 
There'd be war!

906
01:24:39,440 --> 01:24:42,400 
Get her to marry him, Pappa!

907
01:24:47,440 --> 01:24:49,840 
I'll keep my word.

908
01:24:51,360 --> 01:24:54,040 
My daughter will marry you.

909
01:24:55,560 --> 01:24:59,360 
She will sacrifice herself
for the Kingdom, for the family.

910
01:25:04,240 --> 01:25:06,240 
Au revoir.

911
01:25:08,040 --> 01:25:09,800 
Wait!

912
01:25:12,880 --> 01:25:14,880 
Poor little girl.

913
01:25:14,960 --> 01:25:17,240 
She'll get used to him.

914
01:25:17,760 --> 01:25:22,200 
One for us,
one for his Majesty.

915
01:25:26,160 --> 01:25:29,120 
One for us,
one for his Majesty.

916
01:25:37,720 --> 01:25:40,640 
Pull out another, Peter.

917
01:25:40,720 --> 01:25:43,200 
You'll need to renovate the mill.

918
01:25:43,320 --> 01:25:46,480 
One for us,
and one for us too.

919
01:25:52,800 --> 01:25:55,920 
And one each for luck.

920
01:26:00,320 --> 01:26:03,200 
Tomorrow we go to the castle.

921
01:26:03,400 --> 01:26:05,640 
I'm getting married.

922
01:26:14,080 --> 01:26:16,480 
Why are you doing that?

923
01:26:23,560 --> 01:26:25,920 
Thank you, Lucifer!

924
01:26:58,040 --> 01:26:59,920 
Who is it?
- Wait.

925
01:27:00,600 --> 01:27:02,840 
Yes, they're real.

926
01:27:03,040 --> 01:27:05,960 
I have come for my bride.

927
01:27:07,240 --> 01:27:09,680 
I'm marrying this one!

928
01:27:10,960 --> 01:27:14,800 
When I asked for your daughter,
I meant Adela.

929
01:27:15,120 --> 01:27:17,000 
This one?!

930
01:27:17,160 --> 01:27:19,600 
She's the one I'll marry.

931
01:27:20,120 --> 01:27:23,680 
Dear children.
I'll stay on the shelf?!

932
01:27:23,920 --> 01:27:27,400 
I'll think of something.

933
01:27:28,960 --> 01:27:31,360 
I want a husband now!

934
01:27:58,240 --> 01:28:00,400 
It's not fair!

935
01:28:00,480 --> 01:28:03,040 
Angelina, please?
- Excuse me.

936
01:28:04,040 --> 01:28:06,040 
May I have the pleasure?

937
01:28:07,400 --> 01:28:09,240 
With your permission.

938
01:28:09,880 --> 01:28:12,560 
Yes.

939
01:28:13,720 --> 01:28:17,120 
Angelina, a partner for you.

940
01:28:18,280 --> 01:28:20,720 
Interesting, passionate.

941
01:28:27,920 --> 01:28:31,760 
A good thing you didn't marry
that miller.

942
01:28:31,840 --> 01:28:35,320 
How about marrying a Prince?

943
01:28:36,280 --> 01:28:38,760 
Even the Prince of Hell?

944
01:28:38,840 --> 01:28:42,000 
Of course.
I don't believe in hell, you see.

945
01:28:42,320 --> 01:28:44,680 
In that case...

946
01:28:46,480 --> 01:28:48,800 
Lots of happiness.

947
01:28:49,080 --> 01:28:50,520 
Johnny!

948
01:28:50,600 --> 01:28:52,320 
Johnny!

949
01:28:53,560 --> 01:28:56,440 
But that's...
- She'll be fine.

950
01:28:56,640 --> 01:28:58,360 
Johnny!

951
01:28:58,800 --> 01:29:00,720 
I've got to go.

952
01:29:00,800 --> 01:29:02,560 
But...

953
01:29:10,800 --> 01:29:12,520 
Johnny!

954
01:29:16,680 --> 01:29:18,400 
Peter!

955
01:29:31,800 --> 01:29:35,440 
Hell may exist or not,
but it was a good idea.

956
01:29:36,760 --> 01:29:39,560 
If we look around us we see

957
01:29:39,640 --> 01:29:43,240 
that many people would be in need of it.

958
01:29:44,600 --> 01:29:47,840 
It isn't a good thing for people
to think

959
01:29:47,920 --> 01:29:50,600 
that evil can go unpunished.

960
01:29:57,120 --> 01:29:59,320 
I'm your love,

961
01:30:02,160 --> 01:30:04,320 
you are my love, too.

962
01:30:06,640 --> 01:30:09,080 
Why should we stay...

963
01:30:09,360 --> 01:30:12,160 
...why should we stay alone.

964
01:30:20,360 --> 01:30:23,160 
THE END